baseUrl = "http://datascience.skpixel.com"

First I am going to fetch the data from the API using httr library.

visibilityUrl = "http://datascience.skpixel.com/correlation"

visibilityDataRes = GET(visibilityUrl)
visibilityData = fromJSON(rawToChar(visibilityDataRes$content))
head(visibilityData)

Since there is no categorical data for me to predict, I am going to convert the Severity data to categorical values of Fatal and Not Fatal. Assuming that 4 is Fatal and anything below is Not Fatal, I will apply the following filter.

visibilityData <- visibilityData %>% mutate(
    Severity = factor(Severity == '4', labels = c('Not Fatal', 'Fatal'))
  )

head(visibilityData)

I have noticed that majority of the data is Not Fatal. This class imbalance can cause the algorithm to not predict it correctly. I will now trim the non fatal data to balance with the fatal data and merge them together.

trimmedFatalData = visibilityData[(visibilityData$Severity == "Fatal"),]
trimmedNonFatalData = visibilityData[(visibilityData$Severity == "Not Fatal"),]

trimmedNonFatalData <- trimmedNonFatalData[1:329,]
visibilityData <- rbind(trimmedFatalData, trimmedNonFatalData)
visibilityData <- as.data.frame(visibilityData[sample(nrow(visibilityData)), ])
head(visibilityData)
